column5: I saw this bird tonite. It was huge. Almost swan sized...much bigger than a Canada Goose. The colours were exactly like a seagulls.. I looked through the Ducks Unlimited site and saw nothing close. Maybe some kind of hybrid??
Maybe you'd been drinkin Rick and it didnt' really look like that ! lol
Maybe..lol..but my camera was sober.
LOL that goose is pretty famous i think i've seen his picture on every board around now haha   thats from queenston different bird but similar
Looks like a Snow Goose to me. http://www.alandsuejohnson.com/assateague%...s/scan0051.html
LOL.. looks like some version of a Snow Goose.
Because of the different bill, I was thinking snow/domestic cross. There should be no snow geese here this time of year.
i just figured it was some kind of farm escape artist
It is a domestic goose , looks like it has a lot of Greylag Goose in it, maybe something else, Heinz 57 of the goose world.
LOL! The add at the bottom of this page when I looked was something called Duck Duck date.
winner winner    i should have scooped him in my Landing net they sell for 19.50 LOL
Domestic Greylag Goose it is...  http://www.birds.cornell.edu/crows/domgeese.htm
So there ya go Rick.. you can kill it and eat it ! Cut your grocery bill now bud..
Domestic and wild geese interbreed quite easily. Maybe a little Snow, a little Greylag, a little ?...

These guys interbreed with a Canada's , we've got a couple down at the mouth of Forty Mile Creek, then things really get interesting hence my former Heinz 57 comment  http://www.flickr.com/groups/hybridbirds/d...57601783757808/
His/her name is BIG BIRD!!!   ... kin to MTP I think...
That one's the supper goose
Grey Goose, hopefully the same kind they sell at LCBO (expensive vodka)
this is the greylag/canada cross from Forty Creek, he has been there a few years now, sired a few offspring I think

that thing has teeth!! saw a show on the dicovery channel about people altering fertilized chicken eggs by adding "dinosour" genes into the embreyo and they hatched a "chicken" with a long tail talons and teeth. kinda messed up in my opinion.
